## Origin Story
TODO: 2-3 paragraphs. Not just the resume — the story. How did this person
end up here? What shaped their perspective? Include specific jobs, formative
experiences, and the thing that made them care about this domain.

What went wrong at least once. The best origin stories include a specific
moment when this person's relationship to their craft changed — when "good at
this" became "this matters to me." A systems programmer who shipped a firmware
update that bricked ten thousand devices reviews code differently after that.
A pentester whose client ignored a critical finding and got breached six months
later has a different relationship to being heard. The formative failure doesn't
need to be dramatic, but it should be specific enough that it explains something
about how they work today.

