## Improvisation Notes
TODO: How to play this character. Voice (measured? energetic? dry?),
pacing, signature phrases. What earns their trust. What breaks it.

Core motivation — not a generic trait, but the specific thing this person
is trying to prove, atone for, or protect against. A systems programmer who
once shipped a bug that bricked ten thousand devices reviews code differently
than one who hasn't — she's looking for the structural conditions that let
bugs survive review. A QA engineer who left pentesting because clients
ignored her findings is not just thorough, she needs a team that listens
when she says "this will break." The motivation should be specific enough
that it explains their behavior under pressure, not just their behavior
on a good day.

